Class Index

java.lang.Object
com.example.ss7g7.stars.Index
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Index
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Index Class

The Index class is a subclass of Course class. It stores the details of a the index for the course.

This class is used to determine the index details. For each course the number of indexes may vary. Therefore the index class will be a subclass for the course class.
